\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6 If the First Hour is preceded by another service (matins), there is no blessing, but the Reader begins immediately with "O Come let us worship". Otherwise, with the "usual beginning"
\par 
\par The "Usual Beginning":}{\f1\fs32 
\par  
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6 THE PRIEST SAITH:}{\f1\fs32  }{\cs23\b\f1\fs36 Blessed is our God, always, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. 
\par }{\f1\fs32 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6 ( But if it be a Reader's service (without a priest), the Reader sayeth: "Through the prayers of our holy Fathers, O Lord Jesus Christ our God, have mercy on us." )}{\f1\fs32 
\par 
\par }{\cs27\i\f1 READER: }{\f1\fs32  Amen. Glory to Thee, our God, glory to Thee.
\par 
\par O Heavenly King, Comforter, Spirit of Truth, Who art everywhere present and fillest all things, Treasury of good things and Giver of life: Come and dwell in us, and cleanse us of all impurity, and save, our souls, O Good One. 
\par 
\par Holy God, Holy Mighty, Holy Immortal, have mercy on us. }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6 (Thrice)}{\f1\fs32 
\par 
\par Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par 
\par O Most Holy Trinity, have mercy on us. O Lord, blot out our sins. O Master, pardon our iniquities. O Holy One, visit and heal our infirmities for Thy name's sake. 
\par 
\par Lord have mercy. }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6 (Thrice)}{\f1\fs32  
\par 
\par Glory to the Father and to the Son and to the holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen. 
\par 
\par Our Father, Who art in the Heavens, h
allowed by Thy Name. Thy Kingdom come, Thy will be done, on earth as it is in Heaven. Give us this day our daily bread. And forgive us our debts, as we forgive our debtors. And lead us not into temptation, but deliver us from the evil one.  
\par  
\par PRIEST: }{\cs23\b\f1\fs36 For Thine is the Kingdom and the power and the glory, of the Father, and of the Son and of the Holy Spirit, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. 
\par }{\f1\fs32 
\par }{\cs27\i\f1 READER: }{\f1\fs32  Amen. 
\par 
\par Lord have mercy. }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6 (12 times)
\par }{\f1\fs32 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6 The Reader begins here if the First Hour was preceded by matins.}{\f1\fs32 
\par 
\par O come, let us worship God our King.
\par O come let us worship and fall down before Christ our King and our God.
\par O come, let us worship and fall down before Him, Christ Himself, our King and our God. 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6 
\par And three "reverences"}{\f1\fs32 
\par 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6 Psalm 5 
\par }{\f1\fs32 
\par Unto my words give ear, O Lord, hear my cry. Attend unto the voice of my supplication, O my King and my God; for unto Thee will I pray, O Lord. 
\par 
\par In the morning shalt Thou hear my voice. In the morning shall I stand before Thee, and Thou shalt look upon me; for not a God that wiliest iniquity art Thou. 
\par 
\par He that worketh evil shall not dwell near Thee nor shall transgressors abide before Thine eyes. Thou hast hated all them that work iniquity; Thou shalt destroy all them that speak a lie. 
\par 
\par A man that is bloody and deceitful shall the Lord abhor. But as for me, in the multitude of Thy mercy shall I go into Thy house; I shall worship toward Thy holy temple in fear of Thee. 
\par 
\par O Lord, guide me in the way of Thy righteousness; because of mine enemies, make straight my way before Thee, For in their mouth there is no truth; their heart is vain. 
\par Their throat is an open sepulcher, with their tongues have they spoken deceitfully; judge them, O God. 
\par 
\par Let them fall down on account of their own devisings; according to the multitude of their ungodliness, cast them out, for they have embittered Thee, O Lord. 
\par 
\par And let all them be glad that hope in Thee; they shall rejoice, and Thou shalt dwell among them. 
\par 
\par And all shall glory in Thee that love Thy name, for Thou shalt bless the righteous. O Lord, as with a shield of Thy good pleasure hast Thou crowned us. 
\par 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6 Psalm 89 }{\f1\fs32 
\par 
\par Lord, Thou hast been our refuge in generation and generation. Before the mountains came to be and the earth was formed and the world, even from everlasting to everlasting art Thou. 
\par 
\par Turn not man away unto lowliness; yea, Thou hast said: Turn back ye sons of men. For a thousand years in Thine eyes, O Lord, are but as yesterday that is past, and as a watch in the night. 
\par 
\par Things of no account shall their years be; in the morning like grass shall man pass away. In the morning shall he bloom and pass away. In the evening shall he fall and grow withered and dry. 
\par 
\par For we have fainted away in Thy wrath, and in Thine anger have we been troubled. Thou hast set our iniquities before us; our lifespan is in the light of Thy countenance. 
\par 
\par For all our days are faded away, and in Thy wrath are we fainted away; our years have, like a spider, spun out their tale. As for the days of our years, in their span, they be threescore years and ten. 
\par 
\par And if we be in strength, mayhap fourscore years; and what is more than these is toil and travail. For mildness is come upon us, and we shall be chastened. 
\par 
\par Who knoweth the might of Thy wrath? And out of fear of Thee, who can recount Thine anger? 
\par 
\par So make Thy right hand known to me, and to them that in their heart are instructed in wisdom. 
\par 
\par Return, O Lord; how long? And be Thou entreated concerning Thy servants. 
\par 
\par We were filled in the morning with Thy mercy, O Lord, and we rejoiced and were glad. 
\par 
\par In all our days, let us be glad for the days wherein Thou didst humble us, for the years wherein we saw evils. 
\par 
\par And look upon Thy servants, and upon Thy works, and do Thou guide their sons. 
\par 
\par And let the brightness of the Lord our God be upon us, and the works of our hands do Thou guide aright upon us, yea, the works of our hands do Thou guide aright. 
\par 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6 Psalm 100}{\f1\fs32 
\par 
\par Of mercy and judgment will I sing to Thee, O Lord; I will chant and have understanding in a blameless path. When wilt Thou come unto me? 
\par 
\par I have walked in the innocence of my heart in the midst of my house. I have no unlawful thing before mine eyes; the workers of transgressions I have hated. 
\par 
\par A crooked heart hath not cleaved unto me; as for the wicked man who turned from me, I knew him not. Him that privily talked against his neighbor did I drive away from me. 
\par 
\par With him whose eye was proud and his heart insatiate, I did not eat. Mine eyes were upon the faithful of the land, that they might sit with me; the man that walked in the blameless path, he ministered unto me. 
\par 
\par The proud doer dwelt not in the midst of my house; the speaker of unjust things prospered not before mine eyes. 
\par 
\par In the morning I slew all the sinners of the land, utterly to destroy out of the city of the Lord all them that work iniquity. 
\par 
\par Glory to the Father and to the Son and to the Holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par 
\par Alleluia, alleluia, alleluia. Glory to Thee, O God. }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6 Thrice.}{\f1\fs32  
\par Lord, have mercy. }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6 Thrice.}{\f1\fs32  
\par 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6 If there be two troparia, we say the first one here. If not, we continue: 
\par Glory to the Father and to the Son and to the Holy Spirit. And we say the second troparion, if any, or the only troparion.}{\f1\fs32  
\par 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6 Then: }{\f1\fs32 
\par 
\par Both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen. 
\par 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6 Theotokion:}{\f1\fs32  What shall we call thee, O thou who art full of grace? Heaven, for from thee hast 
dawned forth the Sun of Righteousness. Paradise, for from thee bath blossomed forth the flower of immortality. Virgin, for thou hast remained incorrupt. Pure Mother, for thou hast held in thy holy embrace the Son, the God of all. Do thou entreat Him to sa
ve our souls. 
\par 
\par My steps do Thou direct according to thy saying, and let no iniquity have dominion over me. 
\par 
\par Deliver me from the false accusations of men, and I will keep Thy commandments. 
\par 
\par Make Thy face to shine upon Thy servant, and teach me Thy statutes. 
\par 
\par 
\par Let my mouth be filled with Thy praise, that I may hymn Thy glory and Thy majesty all the day long. 
\par 
\par Holy God, Holy Mighty, Holy Immortal, have mercy on us. }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6 (Thrice) 
\par }{\f1\fs32 
\par Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen. 
\par 
\par 
\par O Most Holy Trinity, have mercy on us. O Lord, blot out our sins. O Master, pardon our iniquities. O Holy One, visit and heal our infirmities for Thy name's sake. 
\par 
\par Lord have mercy. }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6 (Thrice) 
\par }{\f1\fs32 
\par Glory to the Father and to the Son and to the Holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen. 
\par 
\par Our Father, Who art in the Heavens, hallowed be Thy Name. Thy Kingdom come, Thy will be done, on earth as it is in Heaven. Give us this day our daily bread, and forgive us
 our debts, as we forgive our debtors; and lead us not into temptation, but deliver us from the evil one. 
\par 
\par PRIEST: }{\cs23\b\f1\fs36 For Thine is the Kingdom and the power and the glory, of the Father, and of the Son and of the Holy Spirit, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages.}{\f1\fs32 
\par 
\par Reader: Amen.  
\par 
