\par 
\par }{\cs15\f1\fs36\cf15 O Thou Who art by nature uncreated, the Fashioner of all, do Thou open our lips that we may proclaim Thy praise while we cry: Holy, Holy, Holy art Thou, O God; through the Theotokos, have mercy on us.}{\f1\fs32    
\par 
\par }{\cs15\f1\fs36\cf15 Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit.
\par 
\par Imitating on earth the Hosts on high, we offer Thee, O Good One, the triumphant song: Holy, Holy, Holy art Thou, O God; through the Theotokos, have mercy on us.
\par 
\par Both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.}{\f1\fs32 
\par 
\par }{\cs15\f1\fs36\cf15 From bed and sleep hast Thou raised me up, O Lord; enlighten my mind and heart, and open my lips that I may hymn Thee, O Holy Trinity: Holy, Holy, Holy art Thou, O God; through the Theotokos, have mercy on us.}{\f1\fs32     
